                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260914-245-off1401 t18260914-245-victim1358"></join>
                     </persName>
                  , from his person
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>JAMES JENNINGS FORWARD. I am a <rs id="t18260914-245-viclabel1403" type="occupation">tailor</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260914-245-victim1358 t18260914-245-viclabel1403"></join>, and live at Hackney. On the evening of the 27th of June I was near <placeName id="t18260914-245-crimeloc1404">Church-street, Shoreditch</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18260914-245-crimeloc1404" type="placeName" value="Church-street, Shoreditch"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18260914-245-crimeloc1404" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260914-245-off1401 t18260914-245-crimeloc1404"></join>, between eleven and twelve o'clock; I stood up at a door-way, out of the rain - two men were there, who asked which way I was going; I told them, and they said they were going the same way; I had not gone far before I found my arms pinioned, my hat taken off, and another put on; I gave an alarm, and the men ran away.</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182609140111"></xptr>
            
                  <persName id="t18260914-245-person1359">
                  BENJAMIN 
                  BEAVIS
               <interp inst="t18260914-245-person1359" type="surname" value="BEAVIS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260914-245-person1359" type="given" value="BENJAMIN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260914-245-person1359" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am headborough. I heard the cry of Stop thief! and saw a person in a white great coat run down an alley; I said, he was gone down the alley, and they went and got him - when he returned there was no hat on his head.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260914-245-person1360">
                  WILLIAM 
                  ANTHONY
               <interp inst="t18260914-245-person1360" type="surname" value="ANTHONY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260914-245-person1360" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260914-245-person1360" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a watchman. I went in company with Buck and Taylor - the prisoner was taken at a door at the bottom of the steps; I saw this hat on his head; I took it off, and gave it to Buck.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260914-245-person1361">
                  JOSEPH 
                  BUCK
               <interp inst="t18260914-245-person1361" type="surname" value="BUCK"></interp>
